	   <tr><td colspan=2>Put all your points into str.  Agi and Dex mean @#%^ to warriors.  Keep agi above 75, as 75 is a border line for AC penalties.  Warriors are tanks, fellas.  Why worry about agi and dex?  If you ask a lot of warriors at high level, they would agreed that str and sta are the only true useful stats.  As for the starting stats of a halfling vs. an ogre?  Halfling has insane agility, but they're useless.  Halfling warriors can tell you that they can dodge (dependant only on dodge skill) or evade attacks (dependant only on AC) far more than other races all they want, but they're just feeding themselves lies.  Those starting agility can only grant them like 6 more AC than an ogre.  But the ogre will get far more hp (which is proportional to both level and sta).  Go for str, sta, AC and you'll be an awesome tank.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
