	   <tr><td colspan=2> This might be changing now. In one of the new messages I heard that weapon skills are going to be based on melee stats now. Meaning their increase will be determined more by your stregnth and dexterity than by your intelligence. Hopefully the painfull cycle of raising each skill per level will be over. As for what to fight to get skill question. I would suggest grabbing some low delay weapons which also mean low damage and getting into a group where your damage doesnt matter.<br><br> A good example of this would be a mostly caster group. Where your main role is to basically just soak up damage. Since you will be hitting fairly quickly your can keep the monster on you while the casters burn it down. I get great gain off anything that is blue-red. Increase is all based on sucessfull attempts at the skill. The longer the battle lasts and/or the more battles you have the more swinging you do, which gives a higer chance for those skills to raise. Don't give up! There is plenty of time in the game to eventually get all those weapon skills where you want them. <br>&nbsp;<br>Walil</td></tr>
