<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9706320929229></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9706320929229><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=1&mid=9706320929229>Short post on melee heavy groups</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=889><span id= >Ashbentiel</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>52 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Oct 4th 12:01 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Just finished playing my 18th rogue in highpass and thought I'd make mention of some of the best groups I've been in so far.<br><br>In Highpass we had two rogues, three warriors, and a shaman. Between the shaman hasting us and healing us we managed to make an unholy ammount of xp in a very very short time with no worries of having to pull a mob off of anyone because they didn't have the hp to tank for a minute. We also dished out damage faster than anything short of 6 wizards chain nuking from an unreachable spot. In short we kicked more butt than anything verant considers a balanced group with no deaths and got more xp (relatively) because all the classes except the shaman had very low xp modifiers.<br><br>Another time I could mention is when my warrior was in paw just after the revamp of the dungeon to higher level mobs. We had two warriors, two paladins, a druid, and a cleric. We had one warrior (me) as priamry tank, meaning he was the one who pulled the trains to us and soaked the majority of the hits. While the other warrior played the secondary tank, meaning he pulled one mob off out of the pull onto himself and then assisted the main tank and soaking one mob's hits, he was also the one to pull anything off the healers. The paladins assisted the main tank and did all of the downtime healing and cleric type buffing, when we had downtime which wasn't very often. The druid cast regen, skin like whatever, stat buffs, snare, and healed the secondary tank. The cleric healed the main tank during the fight and medded. The fights were insane, constant, and just pure fun.<br><br>I must highly recomend this fighting arangement for anywhere that casters are not a major issue and you're not fighting "special" mobs that have to be taken down quickly. Remember, melee classes don't do damage as fast as a caster but we do it alot more efficiently...no resists, no med time, no fizzles, no snaring ourselves or wasting mana nuking a party member on accident, oh and no having to yell "get it off me!!!" every few minutes.<br>&nbsp;<br>Ashbentiel<br>Bard of Tarew Marr<br>"I may make you feel but I can't make you think."  --Jethro Tull</td></tr>
